    %script{src: "demo.js", type: "text/javascript"}

  %body
    .container
      %h1= "Datagrid Demo"

      %p.lead= "Backbone Datagrid is a plugin to organize present data with some controls like sorting, pagging, filtering. "
        %a{link: "http://backbonejs.org", target: "_blank"}= "Backbone"
        = " and "
        %a{link: "https://github.com/marionettejs/backbone.marionette", target: "_blank"}= "Backbone.Marionette"
        = " are used to offer a simple and extensible way to present the data in a structured way. A default styling "
        = "is proposed through the usage of "
        %a{link: "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/", target: "_blank"}= "Twitter Bootstrap"
        = ". This should be easily overriden by your own styling."


      %h2= "Table with default setup"

      %p= "In most of cases, usual components like simple filter, sorting, pagging are used to present data into a table."
        = " Backbone Datagrid offers these components out of the box like shown in the following demo. Every part of the"
        = " plugin implementation could be overriden to provide a custom way to present data."

      .clearfix{id: "dg1"}

      %h2= "Table with duplicate regions on top and bottom"

      %p= "The default components provided by the plugin could be used twice or more on a single data grid. By default,"
        = " the implementation provided automatically synchronized such views as far as they share some common structure and"
        = " styling."

      .clearfix{id: "dg2"}

      %h2= "Table where toolbar and items per page are removed"

      %p= "When some components are not required to present your datagrid, you can easily configure your grid to remove"
        = " the components that you do not want to show. This is done by configuration when you create the data grid"
        = " layout."

      .clearfix{id: "dg3"}

      %h2= "Grid with a totally different markup"

      %p= "That is not so unfrequent to present data under a different markup that usual "
        %code= "&lt;table /&gt;"
        = " tag. The plugin offers"
        = " an easy way to change the layout and the related markup. In the following example, only divs and spans are used"
        = " to present the data. The other components remains usable as they do not manipulate directly the markup of the"
        = " data."

      .clearfix{id: "dg4"}

